<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-11-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-11-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="220" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d220">
                            <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Conger</persName> to
                                    Mr. <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Pekin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-11-19"><hi rend="italic">November 19,
                                        1900</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                            <p>(Mr. Conger reports that by a new Imperial decree, dated November 13,
                                punishment of persons mentioned in Imperial decree of September 25
                                is fixed. In every case the punishment is totally inadequate and is
                                considered as farcical by the diplomatic corps.)</p>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>